that in negotiations

01:49.009 --> 01:50.374
both sides have got
to give a little bit.

01:50.477 --> 01:51.842
POTSIE:
Mmm.

01:51.945 --> 01:54.880
Why, you remember Henry Clay,
right, the Great Compromiser?

01:54.982 --> 01:57.178
Oh, right. He died a pauper.

01:57.284 --> 01:59.981
Oh, give it another shot,
would you?

02:00.087 --> 02:02.055
Hey, Al.

02:02.155 --> 02:03.714
Aw.

02:03.824 --> 02:05.314
Has it come to this?

02:05.425 --> 02:07.393
Look, the-the guys want to
negotiate some more, all right?

02:07.494 --> 02:08.393
Okay. All right.

02:08.495 --> 02:10.190
Fellas, you heard my offer.

02:10.297 --> 02:11.594
Now what do you say?

02:11.698 --> 02:12.824
Go suck an egg.

02:12.933 --> 02:15.300
Oh, yeah? Well, the same to you.

02:15.402 --> 02:16.767
Negotiate, huh?
(blows raspberry)

02:16.870 --> 02:18.429
-(blowing raspberries)
- All right, all right,

02:18.538 --> 02:19.767
that's a start.

02:19.873 --> 02:22.274
Uh, we'll continue this session
later, right?

02:25.679 --> 02:27.044
All right...

02:27.147 --> 02:29.047
yeah... uh!

02:29.149 --> 02:30.708
Get over here.

02:30.817 --> 02:32.376
Not in front of a minor,

02:32.486 --> 02:33.783
-you know what I mean?
-(snaps fingers)

02:33.887 --> 02:37.050
All right. Let me introduce you
to some of my pals here.

02:37.157 --> 02:39.251
Hey. How are you?

02:39.359 --> 02:40.793
This is Bobby, you know?

02:40.894 --> 02:42.020
Peggy's little boy.

02:42.129 --> 02:43.358
Hey, Fonz, what,
did you hire someone

02:43.463 --> 02:44.362
to work on small engines?

02:44.464 --> 02:45.363
Ha, ha, ha.

02:45.465 --> 02:46.762
You get it? With the...

02:46.867 --> 02:50.132
Even in labor disputes,
I still got it.

02:50.237 --> 02:51.602
You must be Ralph.

02:51.705 --> 02:54.037
Hey, hey, he knows you.
(chuckles)

02:54.141 --> 02:56.166
- Yeah, that's right-- and this
here is Potsie, right? -Hi.

02:56.276 --> 02:57.971
- And Richie Cunningham,
good friend. -Hi, Bobby.

02:58.078 --> 02:59.307
All right, guys,
watch this, watch this--

02:59.413 --> 03:01.711
he's gonna knock your socks off.
Give me five.

03:01.815 --> 03:04.443
Put it in your pocket
and don't let nobody hock it.

03:04.551 --> 03:06.110
Whoa.

03:06.219 --> 03:08.449
Well, he's a regular
Shakespeare.

03:08.555 --> 03:10.455
Better, better.
He rhymes.

03:10.557 --> 03:11.956
The Champ taught it to me.

03:12.059 --> 03:14.426
Yeah, well, see, now,
he calls me the Champ

03:14.528 --> 03:16.519
and I call him Kemosabe.

03:18.031 --> 03:18.964
Hey, Kemosabe.

03:19.066 --> 03:20.261
That's really cute.
(chuckles)

03:20.367 --> 03:22.426
Hey, there, Kemosabe.

03:22.536 --> 03:23.628
- Hold it, Weber.
- Yeah?

03:23.737 --> 03:25.728
I call him Kemosabe.

03:25.839 --> 03:26.738
- Ah.
- Right, Fonz.

03:26.840 --> 03:27.636
Hi, there, Bobby.

03:27.741 --> 03:28.765
Thank you.

03:28.875 --> 03:29.967
The jukebox. Can I?

03:30.077 --> 03:32.068
Yeah, let's give it a shot.

03:36.483 --> 03:38.144
(rock 'n' roll song playing)

03:41.088 --> 03:42.249
I did it, Champ!

03:42.355 --> 03:44.517
Yeah, you sure did.
You knocked my socks off.

03:44.624 --> 03:46.922
Why don't we sit down and take
a load off our feet, all right?

03:47.027 --> 03:49.189
Yeah.
Hey, you guys gonna join us?

03:49.296 --> 03:51.390
- Oh, thanks, Fonz.
- Uh, we'd like to Fonz,

03:51.498 --> 03:54.263
-but we got union biz.
- Right.

03:54.367 --> 03:56.768
Get right up in there.

03:56.870 --> 03:58.429
What's with Huey and Dewey?

03:58.538 --> 04:00.131
Ignore 'em, Fonz.

04:00.240 --> 04:01.867
Everybody else is.

04:04.511 --> 04:06.479
BOBBY:
Hey, there's Mom. Hi, Mom.

04:06.580 --> 04:08.480
Hiya, Bobby.

04:08.582 --> 04:10.846
Whoa.

04:10.951 --> 04:12.146
Having fun?

04:12.252 --> 04:14.152
Sure, I'm with the Champ.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.745
Yeah, this is my good friend
Richie Cunningham.

04:16.857 --> 04:18.552
And my good friend Peggy Clark.

04:18.658 --> 04:20.716
How do you do?
Hey, you got a great kid here.

04:20.827 --> 04:22.386
Great? Fabumundo.

04:22.496 --> 04:25.864
We have great times together,
don't we? (chuckles)

04:25.966 --> 04:27.866
Well, we have fabulous times
together too, yeah.

04:27.968 --> 04:29.402
I mean, a little bit different,
you know?

04:29.503 --> 04:30.527
Forget it. Forget it.

04:30.637 --> 04:33.197
Have I got a time planned
for us tonight.

04:33.306 --> 04:34.068
Yeah, what's cookin'?

04:34.174 --> 04:36.074
- Got, uh, movies?
- No.

04:36.176 --> 04:38.736
- Dinner?
- No...

04:38.845 --> 04:41.143
- Dancing...
- Mm-mm.

04:41.248 --> 04:44.149
I thought that we'd all go
to an amusement park.

04:44.251 --> 04:46.219
How's that, huh? Want to go
to an amusement park?

04:46.319 --> 04:48.219
Come on, Mom, we're going
to an amusement park.

04:48.321 --> 04:50.881
- Hey, Fonz, an amusement park?
- Yeah.

04:50.991 --> 04:53.619
All right.

04:53.727 --> 04:55.821
Well, don't worry about it.

04:55.929 --> 04:57.727
He usually gets lost.

05:01.802 --> 05:04.794
Oh, Howard.

05:08.275 --> 05:11.176
Well, I... What-what is wrong

05:11.278 --> 05:14.680
with getting excited
at my first auction?

05:21.621 --> 05:24.522
This is what's wrong, Marion.

05:24.624 --> 05:26.319
It's nostalgia.

05:26.426 --> 05:29.589
And it's gonna give the living
room a whole new look.

05:29.696 --> 05:32.063
It already has.

05:32.165 --> 05:34.497
Now, where shall we put it?

05:34.601 --> 05:37.502
Oh, oh. You guys.

05:37.604 --> 05:40.232
You are not going
to believe this.

05:40.340 --> 05:42.434
Flash, Jenny Piccalo
just told me

05:42.542 --> 05:44.636
that Fonzie is secretly married.

05:44.744 --> 05:46.109
What?!

05:46.213 --> 05:47.772
He has a kid and everything.

05:47.881 --> 05:49.440
Oh, Joanie, don't be ridiculous.

05:49.549 --> 05:51.574
Fonzie is not married.

05:51.685 --> 05:54.052
Well, I don't know
why he never told us.

05:54.154 --> 05:56.782
Marion, are you gonna believe
Jenny Piccalo?

05:56.890 --> 05:57.789
Dad...

05:57.891 --> 06:00.451
scoop-wise, Jenny Piccalo is,

06:00.560 --> 06:02.460
uh, better
than a gossip columnist.

06:02.562 --> 06:04.792
And just about as accurate.

06:04.898 --> 06:07.959
Well, she did know about Liz
and Eddie before Debbie did.

06:08.068 --> 06:09.229
That's right.

06:16.309 --> 06:18.403
That's a beautiful new lamp.

06:18.511 --> 06:22.072
Gives the place
a whole new look.

06:22.182 --> 06:23.741
Oh, Arthur.

06:23.850 --> 06:25.614
Yeah, Mrs. C., what?

06:25.719 --> 06:27.551
We know your secret.

06:27.654 --> 06:29.816
The cat's out of the bag.

06:29.923 --> 06:33.484
Well, I-l knew that was gonna
happen to me sometime, you know?

06:33.593 --> 06:36.085
- You mean it's true?
- Told you so.

06:36.196 --> 06:37.755
Well, now,
I got one problem here.

06:37.864 --> 06:40.094
Exactly what secret is this
we're talking about?

06:40.200 --> 06:43.761
Well, uh, about you being
married and having a child.

06:43.870 --> 06:46.840
Oh, that one.

06:46.940 --> 06:50.171
I only got one problem
with that one.

06:50.277 --> 06:52.371
Come on, Fonz.
Jenny has seen you all over town

06:52.479 --> 06:54.743
with this woman
and-and little boy.

06:54.848 --> 06:56.213
True. Very, very true.

06:56.316 --> 06:57.681
Oh, Arthur.

06:57.784 --> 07:01.015
Howard, we've got to get them
a special wedding present.

07:01.121 --> 07:02.748
Let's give 'em the lamp.

07:04.190 --> 07:08.286
Uh, I'd rather give you, uh,
an explanation, you know?

07:08.395 --> 07:10.295
Like, uh, I met
this fabulous girl, right?-

07:10.397 --> 07:12.764
Peggy Clark-- and she's got
this incredible little boy,

07:12.866 --> 07:15.494
who happens to be most enamored
with me.

07:15.602 --> 07:17.161
- Joanie...
- Right. (chuckles)

07:17.270 --> 07:19.238
I have a lot of rumor-squelching
to do.

07:19.339 --> 07:20.465
- Mm-hmm.
- Sorry, Fonz.

07:20.573 --> 07:24.134
<i>You know, that Jenny Pier-Mo
sure is a gossip.</i>

07:25.145 --> 07:27.512
But what about Peggy's husband?

07:27.614 --> 07:28.706
Gone.

07:28.815 --> 07:31.682
Aw, to be widowed
and with a child.

07:31.785 --> 07:33.412
Oh, no, no, no, Mrs. C.,
not that kind of gone.

07:33.520 --> 07:36.490
Gone, like a bum;
Splitsville; separated.

07:36.589 --> 07:39.354
Went out for ice cream two years
ago and never came back.

07:39.459 --> 07:43.692
Well, that is one of the nicest
things about Howard.

07:43.797 --> 07:47.529
Whenever he goes out,
he always comes back.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.301
Yeah, look, uh, the reason
I came down here,

07:51.404 --> 07:52.894
you know, you being parents
and everything,

07:53.006 --> 07:54.633
I got Bobby playing upstairs,
right?

07:54.741 --> 07:58.041
Now, he's asking me
a lot of questions, you know?

07:58.144 --> 08:01.910
His latest one is,
"Where do babies come from?"

08:02.015 --> 08:03.540
Now, what do you tell a kid?

08:03.650 --> 08:07.518
Oh, well, that's, uh, uh...
Marion?

08:07.620 --> 08:09.179
Yes.

08:09.289 --> 08:11.724
Uh... Howard?

08:11.825 --> 08:13.122
I get your drift.
I get your drift.

08:13.226 --> 08:14.751
I know exactly
what I'm gonna do.

08:14.861 --> 08:16.022
I'm going back upstairs.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.426
Every time
he asks me a question,

08:17.530 --> 08:19.020
I'll make him some popcorn.

08:19.132 --> 08:21.760
I'll ignore the whole subject,
just like parents do, you know.

08:21.868 --> 08:23.199
Whoa, hey!

08:29.242 --> 08:30.971
All right, I'll hold it,
you turn it there, right?

08:31.077 --> 08:32.272
- Looks good.
- Yeah.

08:32.379 --> 08:35.371
Hey, you never did tell me
where babies come from.

08:35.482 --> 08:37.381
Uh-oh.

08:37.484 --> 08:38.417
Never mind.

08:38.518 --> 08:41.215
I don't want any more popcorn.

08:41.321 --> 08:42.755
Smart kid, huh?

08:42.856 --> 08:44.756
Well, I think the bridge
is ready now, huh?

08:44.858 --> 08:46.019
You do the honors.

08:46.126 --> 08:47.321
Okay.

08:47.427 --> 08:48.952
(sings fanfare)

08:49.062 --> 08:52.259
The Champ Kemosabe Bridge
is now open!

08:52.365 --> 08:53.264
Hey, all right.

08:53.366 --> 08:54.527
Lift it up.

08:54.634 --> 08:56.295
Now we need a boat
to come through.

08:56.403 --> 08:57.336
A boat, yeah.

08:57.437 --> 08:59.599
What am I gonna use for a boat?

08:59.706 --> 09:01.333
Can you be a boat, Champ?

09:01.441 --> 09:03.466
You want me to be a boat, huh?

09:03.576 --> 09:05.476
All right, I'll be a boat.

09:05.578 --> 09:07.273
First thing I got to do,
you understand,

09:07.380 --> 09:10.611
is, uh, just check for,
uh, stowaways, you know.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.708
Just be a minute.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.717
And I'll, uh... I'll just pull
these down here, you know,

09:17.824 --> 09:20.657
batten down my hatches, right?

09:20.760 --> 09:23.388
Always got to
batten down the hatch.

09:23.496 --> 09:24.895
Want me to be a boat?

09:24.998 --> 09:27.023
(chuckles)

09:27.133 --> 09:29.329
(clears throat)

09:30.637 --> 09:32.628
(imitating boat engine)

